<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>

<section xml:id="sec-rational-domain" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
    <title>Domain of Rational Functions</title>

    <alert>Domain "issues" include vertical asymptotes and holes.</alert>
    <definition>
        <title>Vertical Asymptote</title>

        <statement>
            <p>
                The line <m>x=a</m> is a <alert>vertical asymptote</alert> of the graph of a function <m>f</m> if <m>f(x)</m> increases or decreases <em>without bound</em> as <m>x</m> approaches <m>a</m>.
            </p>
        </statement>
    </definition>

    <blockquote>
        <p>
            <image source="img/VA1.jpg" width="50%"/>\includegraphics[height=2in]{img/VA2.jpg}
            </p>
        </blockquote>

        <definition>
            <title>Hole</title>

            <statement>
                <p>
                    A <alert>hole</alert> (empty circle) in the graph of <m>f(x)</m> may also occur for values of <m>x</m> which make both the <em>numerator <alert>and</alert> denominator</em> zero.
                </p>
            </statement>

            <p>
                The graph of the original <m>R(x)</m> and its simplified form are identical <em>except for any holes</em>.
            </p>
        </definition>
    </section>